.TH arctgz 7 "2026-07-19" "arctgz 0.4.0" "Miscellaneous Information Manual"
.SH NAME
arctgz \- safety-first project initialisation, configuration management, archival compilation and extraction library for the arctgz archive format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{\fP
\fB    init, load_config, save_config, compile, extract,\fP
\fB    ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry, ArctgzError\fP
\fB};\fP
\fBuse std::path::Path;\fP

\fBfn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn compile(\fP
\fB    project_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    output_dir: Option<&Path>,\fP
\fB    force: bool\fP
\fB) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn extract(\fP
\fB    archive_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    output_dir: &Path,\fP
\fB    force: bool\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzConfig {\fP
    \fBpub name:    String,\fP
    \fBpub version: String,\fP
    \fBpub include: Vec<String>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzManifest {\fP
    \fBpub name:    String,\fP
    \fBpub version: String,\fP
    \fBpub created: DateTime<Utc>,\fP
    \fBpub files:   BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct FileEntry {\fP
    \fBpub size:   u64,\fP
    \fBpub sha512: String,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum ArctgzError { ... }\fP
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The arctgz library provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project: scaffolding, configuration, compilation into a compressed archive, and verified extraction.
.PP
All operations enforce strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to prevent corruption and TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use) races.
.PP
The core functionality includes:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBinit\fP() \(en scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.
.IP \(bu
\fBload_config\fP() \(en read and validate an existing project configuration.
.IP \(bu
\fBsave_config\fP() \(en atomically write a validated configuration back to disk.
.IP \(bu
\fBcompile\fP() \(en bundle the project files and configuration into a signed (SHA-512) compressed archive.
.IP \(bu
\fBextract\fP() \(en unpack an archive, verifying every file's integrity against the embedded manifest and preventing path traversal attacks.
.PP
All paths are resolved with \fBstd::fs::canonicalize\fP() (equivalent to \fBrealpath\fP(3)), so symbolic links are followed during the home-directory confinement check.
The library is fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.
.SH INSTALLATION
This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:
.PP
.nf
\fBcurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash\fP
.fi
.PP
The script places \fBarctgz.7\fP into \fB/usr/local/share/man/man7/\fP and updates the man database.
To uninstall, run:
.PP
.nf
\fBcurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall\fP
.fi
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
\fBinit\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Initialises a new arctgz project at \fIproject_path\fP.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
A reference to a \fBstd::path::Path\fP.
The path must not be empty and must reside (after canonicalisation) under the current user's home directory.
If the path does not exist, it will be created; otherwise it must be a directory.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, skip the non-empty directory check.
However, an existing \fBarctgz.init\fP file will still cause an \fBAlreadyInitialized\fP error.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP describing the failure.
.RE
.PP
Side effects (only after all safety checks pass):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Creates the project directory (and parents, if needed).
.IP \(bu
Creates the \fBinclude/\fP subdirectory.
.IP \(bu
Writes a default \fBarctgz.init\fP configuration file atomically (using \fBcreate_new(true)\fP).
.RE
.PP
Security checks (performed before any filesystem modification):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Home directory confinement \(en the canonicalised project path must start with the canonicalised home directory.
Symlink attacks are neutralised.
.IP \(bu
Path validity \(en rejects empty paths, and rejects existing files (as opposed to directories).
.IP \(bu
Directory emptiness (unless \fBforce\fP is \fBtrue\fP).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBload_config\fP(\fIproject_path\fP)
.RS
Reads and validates the \fBarctgz.init\fP file from the given project directory.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
Path to the project root (must contain an \fBarctgz.init\fP file).
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(ArctgzConfig)\fP if the file exists, contains valid JSON, and passes \fBvalidate()\fP.
On failure, returns an \fBArctgzError\fP variant (\fBConfigNotFound\fP, \fBConfigLoadError\fP, or \fBConfigValidation\fP).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBsave_config\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIconfig\fP)
.RS
Writes a validated \fBArctgzConfig\fP back to the project's \fBarctgz.init\fP file atomically.
The operation first writes the JSON to a temporary file (\fBarctgz.tmp\fP) and then renames it over the original.
This prevents corruption if the process crashes mid-write.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
Path to the project root.
.TP
\fIconfig\fP
An \fBArctgzConfig\fP instance to save.
Must pass \fBvalidate()\fP before saving.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (\fBConfigValidation\fP, \fBConfigSaveError\fP, or \fBJson\fP).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBcompile\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Compiles the project into a compressed, integrity-verified arctgz archive (\fB.artgz\fP).
.PP
The function:
.IP \(bu 2
Loads the project configuration via \fBload_config\fP().
.IP \(bu
Collects the \fBarctgz.init\fP file and all files listed in the \fBinclude\fP array, recursively adding directories while rejecting symbolic links.
.IP \(bu
Computes a SHA-512 hash for every file and records size + hash in an \fBArctgzManifest\fP.
.IP \(bu
Creates a gzip-compressed tar archive containing the files and the \fBmanifest.json\fP entry.
.IP \(bu
Writes the archive atomically via a temporary file and rename.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
Path to the project root.
.TP
\fIoutput_dir\fP
Optional output directory.
If \fBNone\fP, the archive is placed in \fBproject_path/dist/\fP.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, overwrite an existing archive; otherwise fail if the archive already exists.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(PathBuf)\fP containing the full path to the created archive, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (including \fBIncludeFileNotFound\fP, \fBSymlinkNotAllowed\fP, or \fBIo\fP for an already-existing archive when \fBforce\fP is \fBfalse\fP).
.RE
.PP
Safety:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Symlinks are rejected to prevent reference leaks outside the project.
.IP \(bu
The entire archive is written atomically; a crash mid-write leaves no partial archive.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBextract\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP, \fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Extracts a previously compiled arctgz archive, verifying the integrity of every file and guarding against path traversal attacks.
.PP
The function:
.IP \(bu 2
Opens and decompresses the archive.
.IP \(bu
Locates the embedded \fBmanifest.json\fP and deserialises it.
.IP \(bu
Checks that every file path in the archive is relative and does not contain \fB..\fP (parent directory) components; rejects absolute paths.
.IP \(bu
Verifies that all files listed in the manifest are present in the archive and vice versa.
.IP \(bu
Recomputes the SHA-512 hash of each file and compares it to the manifest entry; a mismatch aborts with \fBChecksumMismatch\fP.
.IP \(bu
Writes files to \fIoutput_dir\fP, creating subdirectories as needed, and refusing to overwrite existing files unless \fBforce\fP is \fBtrue\fP.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIarchive_path\fP
Path to the \fB.artgz\fP archive.
.TP
\fIoutput_dir\fP
Destination directory; will be created if it does not exist.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, overwrite existing files; otherwise abort on conflict.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (\fBManifestNotFound\fP, \fBChecksumMismatch\fP, \fBExtractError\fP for unsafe paths, or \fBIo\fP for file conflicts).
.RE
.RE
.SH TYPES
.TP
\fBArctgzConfig\fP
Represents the project configuration stored in \fBarctgz.init\fP.
.PP
Fields:
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP
Project name (default \fB"untitled"\fP).
Valid characters: alphanumeric, \fB-\fP, and \fB_\fP.
Maximum length 255 characters.
.TP
\fBversion\fP
Semantic version string (default \fB"0.1.0"\fP), validated against the \fBsemver\fP crate.
.TP
\fBinclude\fP
List of relative resource paths (default \fB[]\fP).
Each path must be relative, must not contain \fB..\fP (parent directory) components, and the list may contain at most 100 entries.
.RE
.PP
\fBvalidate\fP()
.br
Validates all fields according to the rules above.
Returns \fBOk(())\fP or an \fBArctgzError::ConfigValidation\fP with a human-readable message.
.PP
The struct is serialised/deserialised with \fB#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]\fP, so unknown JSON keys in the configuration file will cause a deserialisation error.
.TP
\fBArctgzManifest\fP
Embedded inside every compiled archive as \fBmanifest.json\fP.
.RS
.PP
Fields:
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP
Project name (copied from config).
.TP
\fBversion\fP
Project version (copied from config).
.TP
\fBcreated\fP
UTC timestamp of archive creation (\fBchrono::DateTime<Utc>\fP).
.TP
\fBfiles\fP
A \fBBTreeMap\fP mapping archived paths (relative strings) to \fBFileEntry\fP records.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBFileEntry\fP
Metadata for a single file in the archive.
.RS
.PP
Fields:
.RS
.TP
\fBsize\fP
File size in bytes.
.TP
\fBsha512\fP
Hexadecimal string of the file's SHA-512 hash.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBArctgzError\fP
An enumeration covering all failure cases.
Each variant holds a descriptive message (or source error) to aid debugging.
.PP
Variants:
.RS
.TP
\fBIo(std::io::Error)\fP
Filesystem I/O error (e.g., creating directories, writing files, archive already exists).
.TP
\fBJson(serde_json::Error)\fP
JSON serialisation or deserialisation failure.
.TP
\fBAlreadyInitialized\fP
An \fBarctgz.init\fP file already exists in the target directory during \fBinit\fP().
.TP
\fBInvalidPath(String)\fP
The supplied path is empty or is an existing file, not a directory.
.TP
\fBPathNotAllowed(String)\fP
The canonicalised project path lies outside the user's home directory.
.TP
\fBDirectoryNotEmpty(String)\fP
The target directory exists, is not empty, and \fBforce\fP was \fBfalse\fP.
.TP
\fBConfigValidation(String)\fP
A configuration validation rule failed (e.g., invalid name, version, or include).
.TP
\fBConfigNotFound(String)\fP
\fBload_config\fP() could not find the \fBarctgz.init\fP file.
.TP
\fBConfigLoadError(String)\fP
\fBload_config\fP() encountered an I/O error or invalid JSON.
.TP
\fBConfigSaveError(String)\fP
\fBsave_config\fP() failed during the write or rename step.
.TP
\fBSymlinkNotAllowed(String)\fP
A symbolic link was encountered during archive compilation; symlinks are forbidden.
.TP
\fBIncludeFileNotFound(String)\fP
A file listed in the \fBinclude\fP array does not exist on disk during compilation.
.TP
\fBManifestNotFound\fP
The archive being extracted does not contain a \fBmanifest.json\fP entry.
.TP
\fBChecksumMismatch(String, String, String)\fP
A file's actual SHA-512 hash does not match the one recorded in the manifest.
The three fields are: file path, expected hash, actual hash.
.TP
\fBExtractError(String)\fP
Generic extraction failure (unsafe path, missing file, etc.).
.RE
.RE
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS Basic initialisation
.nf
\fBuse std::path::Path;\fP
\fBuse arctgz;\fP

\fBfn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\fP
    \fBlet project_path = Path::new("./my-project");\fP
    \fBarctgz::init(project_path, false)?;\fP
    \fBprintln!("Project created.");\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.PP
After running the above, the directory looks like:
.nf
\fBmy-project/\fP
\fB|-- arctgz.init\fP
\fB\`-- include/\fP
.fi
.SS Editing configuration
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{load_config, save_config};\fP

\fBfn configure(project: &std::path::Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {\fP
    \fBlet mut config = load_config(project)?;\fP
    \fBconfig.name = "hello-world".into();\fP
    \fBconfig.include.push("assets".into());\fP
    \fBsave_config(project, &config)?;\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.SS Compiling and extracting
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{compile, extract};\fP

\fBfn roundtrip(project: &std::path::Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {\fP
    \fBlet archive = compile(project, None, false)?;\fP
    \fBlet out_dir = project.parent().unwrap().join("output");\fP
    \fBextract(&archive, &out_dir, false)?;\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBarctgz.init\fP
JSON configuration file.
Written atomically by \fBinit\fP() and \fBsave_config\fP().
The library never truncates an existing file unless explicitly overwritten via \fBsave_config\fP().
.TP
\fBinclude/\fP
An empty directory created during initialisation.
It is intended to hold resource files for later compilation/archiving.
.TP
\fBdist/<name>-<version>.artgz\fP
Default output location for compiled archives (when \fIoutput_dir\fP is \fBNone\fP).
.TP
\fBmanifest.json\fP
Embedded inside every \fB.artgz\fP archive; contains the project metadata and integrity records.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBHOME\fP (Unix) / \fBUSERPROFILE\fP (Windows)
The library obtains the current user's home directory through the \fBdirs\fP crate.
If the variable is not set, a platform-specific fallback is attempted.
If no home directory can be determined, \fBinit\fP() will fail with \fBPathNotAllowed\fP for any path (even relative ones) because confinement cannot be verified.
.SH SECURITY
.IP \(bu 2
Path confinement: only paths inside the canonicalised home directory are allowed for initialisation.
Symlink traversal is fully mitigated by canonicalising both the project path and the home directory.
.IP \(bu
No side effects before validation: \fBinit\fP() resolves the path and performs all security checks before creating any directories.
Thus, even a failed call with a path outside the home directory will not leave unwanted directories on disk.
.IP \(bu
Atomic configuration writes: the use of \fBcreate_new(true)\fP for \fBinit\fP() prevents TOCTOU attacks when creating the initial config.
\fBsave_config\fP() and \fBcompile\fP() write to a temporary file and rename, ensuring the target file is never left in an incomplete state.
.IP \(bu
Archive integrity: every file in the archive is hashed with SHA-512.
The manifest is embedded and verified during extraction; any mismatch aborts with \fBChecksumMismatch\fP.
.IP \(bu
Path traversal prevention: \fBextract\fP() rejects any archived path that is absolute or contains \fB..\fP components, preventing zip-slip attacks.
.IP \(bu
Symlink rejection: \fBcompile\fP() refuses to include symbolic links, ensuring archives contain only regular files and directories.
.IP \(bu
Input validation: configuration fields are strictly validated.
Unknown JSON keys are rejected, preventing accidental or malicious settings from entering the project metadata.
.SH NOTES
The library is intended to be used as a building block for higher-level tools.
It does not impose any locking mechanism; concurrent calls on the same directory may race (see \fBTOCTOU\fP considerations in the security section).
Users should serialise access when operating on the same project from multiple processes or threads.
.SH VERSION
arctgz 0.4.0 \(en full project lifecycle: initialisation, configuration management, archive compilation with SHA-512 integrity, and verified extraction.
Future releases may add cryptographic signing and post-extraction recipes.
