.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
The \fBinclude/\fP directory is always created empty; files must be added manually before compilation.
.IP \(bu
Concurrent \fBinit\fP calls on the same path are not serialised and may lead to one process failing with \fBAlreadyInitialized\fP while another has already created the directory.
.IP \(bu
The library does not clean up the \fBinclude/\fP directory if the configuration write fails halfway through initialisation.
.IP \(bu
Archive format does not yet include cryptographic signatures; integrity is based solely on SHA-512 hashes.
